HEADWORD: astrocytoma
<hw>astrocytoma</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a tumor of nervous tissue
derived from interstitial cells, in which the cells are relatively
well-differentiated and resemble astrocytes. The occur primarily in the
crebrum and cerebellum.</def> <au>Stedman</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

